# overlay-platform — project context

Next.js web app for **Overlay**. Pairs with sibling backend **`overlay-services`** (NestJS + MongoDB).

## Sibling repos

| Repo | Role | Local path (typical) |
|------|------|----------------------|
| **`overlay-platform`** (this repo) | React UI, auth, API client, overlay renderers | `…/overlay/overlay-platform` |
| **`overlay-services`** | Backend API — DTOs, validation, guards, MongoDB | `…/overlay/overlay-services` |

**HTTP contracts live in `overlay-services`.** Read that repo before inventing request/response shapes. API base: `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` → typically `http://localhost:3001/api/v1` in dev. Canonical backend context: **`overlay-services/.cursor/rules/overlay-context.mdc`**.

## Product

Overlay desacopla el contenido de la web de la forma que el publisher eligió. Toma cualquier página, extrae su contenido como data portable (Firecrawl vía backend), y lo vuelve a pintar según quién lo está leyendo.

Cada **template** del backend tiene un `templateKey` (`vc`, `tramite`, `shopper`, …) y un `extractionSchema`. En el frontend, cada `templateKey` mapea a un componente React que pinta exactamente la forma de ese JSON. Reglas del template:

- **structure** — qué campos mostrar, orden, énfasis, ocultar
- **style** — tipografía, tema, colores, layout

## Stack

- Next.js (App Router) + TypeScript
- API client: `ServicesProvider` + `src/data/api/server/`
- Auth: cookie/session via JWT from **`overlay-services`**
- i18n: `src/messages/en.json`, `es.json`; locale via `src/proxy.ts`

## Backend data model (read-only reference)

```
User → Template (owner nullable = built-in)
Source → Snapshot (cache scrape)
Template + Snapshot → Overlay (extractedData + render)
```

Cache: snapshot por URL, overlay por par `(template, snapshot)`. Ver schemas en `overlay-services/src/{templates,sources,snapshots,overlays}/`.

## Overlay domain (frontend)

- **`templateKey` → componente** — cada intención de lectura tiene su renderer (p. ej. `VcView`, `TramiteView`, `ShopperView`)
- Consume `GET/POST /overlays`, `GET /templates` del backend
- Aplica `structure` y `style` del template al render (reordenar, resaltar, tema)

*(Renderers y rutas de overlay se añaden conforme crezca el producto.)*

## Environment

- `src/config/env.ts`: `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL`
- Requires **`overlay-services`** on port 3001 for auth and API calls

## App shell

- **`/`**: public landing — `src/components/landing/` + `src/content/landing.ts`
- **`/dashboard`**: authenticated home — `AuthGuard` + `HomeShell`
- **Public routes**: `/`, `/sign-in`, `/sign-up`, `/auth/google/callback` — see `AuthGuard` and `src/proxy.ts`
- **Locale proxy**: `src/proxy.ts` strips `/en` and `/es` prefixes; sets `NEXT_LOCALE` cookie
- **Client state**: `ServicesProvider`; API in `src/data/api/server/`; auth user via `normalizeAuthMeUser`

## Styling

- Light theme tokens in `src/app/globals.css` (`--app-*`)
- Component layout: `docs/COMPONENTS.md`

## Agent guidelines

- Minimize scope; match `ServicesProvider`, `AuthGuard`, `@/components/...` patterns
- New overlay UI → isolated components under `src/components/<feature>/`
- API changes → coordinate with **`overlay-services`** (`docs/README.md` there)
